title: Grateful Dead Live at Golden Hall, Community Concourse on 1979-11-23
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, They Love Each Other, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, High Time, Minglewood Blues, Stagger Lee, Easy To Love You, Looks Like Rain-> Deal

Set 2

The Music Never Stopped-> Sugaree, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Black Peter-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Deep Phenomenal recording....Phil's deep and all encompassing rib rattling bass is one of my fondest memories from this era...and this is the closest I've ever heard. Thank you for this wonderful gift!

Ferocious  Now This Is A 5 Star Recording And Show. Phil's Bass Attack Is Ferocious. The Energy From The Whole Band Takes Us To Plateau Of The Rock 'n' Roll Dead That Emerged As Brent Became Comfortable With The Band And The Band With Him. Great Versions Abound. Sugaree Is Outstanding. Just The Follow The Bouncing Bass And Sing Along.
In the Beginning My first show.
